@NODE bekanntefehler "Bekannte Fehler"

@{b} Bekannte Fehler@{ub}

 CheckArc ist eine sehr komplexe Scriptdatei, daher sind Fehler, die
 den Programmablauf durcheinanderbringen, gut möglich. Hier eine 
 Liste der Fehler, die schon bekannt sind:
 
 - Endet eine Datei z.B. mit der Zeichenkette ".lha" und ist kein
   LhA-Archiv, so wird diese Datei als defektes Archiv protokolliert.
   Es ist also dann zu überprüfen, ob es sich wirklich um eine Archivdatei
   handelt. Dies ist eigentlich kein Fehler von CheckArc.
   
 Wenn Sie noch weitere Fehler gefunden haben, benachrichtigen Sie
 bitte den @{"Autor" link autor}.

@ENDNODE

@NODE knownbugs "Known bugs"

@{b} Known bugs@{ub}

 CheckArc is a very complex script file, so it is possible that it
 contains some errors. Here is a list of the known bugs:
 
 - If a file ends with a typical archive extension (e.g. '.lha'), and
   the file is actually not an archive, this file will be marked as
   a defect archive. Please check manually if this is an archive or
   not. This is not CheckArc's fault.
 
 For further bugreports, please contact the @{"author" link author}.

@ENDNODE

@NODE history "History"
	
@{b} History@{ub}

 Version 1.8: Create a temp directory for the cruncher and the stats
              files in the RAM:, name is given by the process number.
              The check script file will be unique, also dependant
              of the process number. So CheckArc may be startet more
              than once.
              Check script will be shorter: The fail operations are
              executed with a seperate script. This may speed down
              (AmigaDOS will create $tick-files in T:), but only if a
              defective archive will be found.
              Defective archives will be marked with a 'filenote'.
              LzX: Corrected the position of the "-q" option.
 Version 1.7: Switch LOWPRI: Sets task priority for LhA/LzX to -1
              Priority can be selected via requester
              Log file: open file error handled, check up for an
              existing file immediately after selection
              Search procedure improved: only #?.<arctype> files
              will be tested (before: all files containing the
              pattern .<arctype>"
 Version 1.5: Highlighted dot if archive contains an error ;)
              MultiView will be startet with 'run', CheckArc will
              terminate itself immediately
 Version 1.4: Little bug: temp. script not deleted on break
              Default Log file now placed in the current directory
 Version 1.3: Many output messages implemented
              Found cruncher will be copied automatically
              Abort possible when creating script file
              Bug with NEWLOG removed
              Progress indicator while checking archives
 Version 1.2: "SAVEMODE" for log file selection
              Removed error at cruncher selection
              Language Support (deutsch/english)
 Version 1.1: First public release
              
@ENDNODE
